translate francais start01:

    # "...They're gone. Everyone's gone. My body aches, but I'm still alive." id start01
    "Le froid glacial de la cabane m'infiltre dans les os. Mais cela ne peut pas aggraver mon esprit engourdi." id start01

# game/script.rpy:66
translate francais start02:

    # "The books! They're still here. I should burn them, to make sure those words are never read again. I never thought I'd be one to start burning books, but after what happened..." id start02
    "Depuis des années, je me retrouve piégé dans cette montagne, pourrissant comme un cadavre." id start02

# game/script.rpy:76
translate francais light01:

    # "My fingers are numb from the cold. I need this fire. I need to feel warm again." id light01
    "Je dois terminer encore un autre jour comme ça ?" id light01

# game/script.rpy:79
translate francais light02:

    # "My parents were trying to work out how the ancient words might be pronounced. I never thought they would get it right. We never imagined those words could have...power." id light02
    "Chaque nuit, je m'en glisse et remets tout en place. Ma chasse au trésor et mes regrets peuvent recommencer à nouveau chaque matin dans la neige fraîche." id light02

# game/script.rpy:80
translate francais light03:

    # "When that creature came out, I lost everything. All because of these stupid books. Now my family is lost, and the creature is missing too. What am I supposed to do now?" id light03
    "Peut-être que demain sera un autre jour." id light03

# game/script.rpy:95
translate francais lit_fire_ee62ea94:

    # "I was going to burn the books, but I ended up reading them..."
    "I was going to burn the books, but I ended up reading them..."

# game/script.rpy:99
translate francais lit_fire_4e8f5bee:

    # "This knowledge is too dangerous. I don't want anyone else to lose everything the way I did."
    "This knowledge is too dangerous. I don't want anyone else to lose everything the way I did."

# game/script.rpy:102
translate francais lit_fire_296deee8:

    # "Even though they cost me everything, I can't destroy the knowledge they hold."
    "Even though they cost me everything, I can't destroy the knowledge they hold."

# game/script.rpy:103
translate francais lit_fire_a36381d8:

    # "In fact, they might be the only way to discover how to stop the... creature."
    "In fact, they might be the only way to discover how to stop the... creature."

# game/script.rpy:104
translate francais lit_fire_76234497:

    # "Or maybe not. But either way, I don't want to lose what my parents worked hard to uncover."
    "Or maybe not. But either way, I don't want to lose what my parents worked hard to uncover."

translate francais strings:

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "Our axe. Mom and dad used to have contests to see who could chop wood faster. We'd keep score, counting in a different language every time."
    new "Si seulement j'avais le courage d'ensevelir la hache quelque part pour apaiser la misère."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "I might need this kindling. Normal books catch fire easily, but these books might have tricks up their sleeves."
    new "Éclats de bois lamentables tombés dans la neige. Ils aideront à allumer un feu, mais n'arrêteront pas les vents frigides."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "My flashlight. I grabbed it when I ran from the cabin last night. I dropped it when I tripped. It doesn't work anymore."
    new "Une lampe torche cassée. Elle m'a donné de l'espoir quand je l'ai vue pour la première fois. Actuellement, ça me rappelle simplement que moi aussi je bloque dans l'obscurité. Mais je ne peux pas profiter de pièces de rechange pour redevenir de nouveau entier."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "Wood for the fire. Wood. Holz. Hout. Madera. Lignum. A lot of good that does me now. How do you say “Go away” to a…whatever that was?"
    new "Je suis obligé de anéantir mes environs pour survivre. Pathétique."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "We usually snuggle up with this blanket on the couch. Could the blast have thrown it this far?"
    new "Cela était gardé dans la cabane au début. Après la première année, je ne pouvais plus supporter de la regarder, alors je l'ai jetée dehors. Parfois je fais semblant de juste l'avoir trouvée, parfois j'essaye de la débarrasser. Ça ne fait pas de différence ; rien ne change."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "My parents made this for me when I was little. It was on a shelf in my room, but now it's way out here..."
    new "Une carcasse vide, forcée de faire des mouvements par quelque puissance qu'elle ne peut pas contrôler ou comprendre. Comment pertinent."

    # game/script.rpy:21
    old "These rocks were from the ritual. They said they were just studying it; they never meant to actually perform the rite!"
    new "Un bon rocher tranchant. Bon pour allumer des feux. Bon pour couper. Mal pour les couards."

    # game/script.rpy:42
    old "I wonder if wolves have a language? Probably not. If they did, my parents would have known it."
    new "Quand est-ce que ces créatures vont s'approcher enfin assez pour amener tout ça à la fin ? J'essaye de les approcher, mais ils fuient quand je deviens proche."

    # game/script.rpy:43
    old "It looks like nothing happened, like there was no blast. I need to get a fire going in here if I want to destroy those books."
    new "Un trou inutile dans le monde, sans tout ce dont j'ai besoin pour allumer un feu."

    # game/script.rpy:96
    old "What should I do with the books?"
    new "What should I do with the books?"

    # game/script.rpy:96
    old "Burn them."
    new "Burn them."

    # game/script.rpy:96
    old "Keep them."
    new "Keep them."

